28AudioRtpReceiver::AudioRtpReceiver(rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
29 std::string receiver_id,
30 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids,
31 bool is_unified_plan)
32 : AudioRtpReceiver(worker_thread,
33 receiver_id,
34 CreateStreamsFromIds(std::move(stream_ids)),
35 is_unified_plan) {}
36
37AudioRtpReceiver::AudioRtpReceiver(
38 rtc::Thread* worker_thread,
39 const std::string& receiver_id,
40 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>& streams,
41 bool is_unified_plan)
42 : worker_thread_(worker_thread),
43 id_(receiver_id),
44 source_(rtc::make_ref_counted<RemoteAudioSource>(
45 worker_thread,
46 is_unified_plan
47 ? RemoteAudioSource::OnAudioChannelGoneAction::kSurvive
48 : RemoteAudioSource::OnAudioChannelGoneAction::kEnd)),
49 track_(AudioTrackProxyWithInternal<AudioTrack>::Create(
50 rtc::Thread::Current(),
51 AudioTrack::Create(receiver_id, source_))),
52 cached_track_enabled_(track_->enabled()),
53 attachment_id_(GenerateUniqueId()),
54 worker_thread_safety_(PendingTaskSafetyFlag::CreateDetachedInactive()) {
55 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_);
56 RTC_DCHECK(track_->GetSource()->remote());
57 track_->RegisterObserver(this);
58 track_->GetSource()->RegisterAudioObserver(this);
59 SetStreams(streams);
60}
61
62AudioRtpReceiver::~AudioRtpReceiver() {
63 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
64 RTC_DCHECK(stopped_);
65 RTC_DCHECK(!media_channel_);
66
67 track_->GetSource()->UnregisterAudioObserver(this);
68 track_->UnregisterObserver(this);
69}
70
71void AudioRtpReceiver::OnChanged() {
72 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
73 if (cached_track_enabled_ != track_->enabled()) {
74 cached_track_enabled_ = track_->enabled();
75 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
76 worker_thread_safety_,
77 [this, enabled = cached_track_enabled_, volume = cached_volume_]() {
78 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
79 Reconfigure(enabled, volume);
80 }));
81 }
82}
83
84// RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_)
85void AudioRtpReceiver::SetOutputVolume_w(double volume) {
86 RTC_DCHECK_GE(volume, 0.0);
87 RTC_DCHECK_LE(volume, 10.0);
88 ssrc_ ? media_channel_->SetOutputVolume(*ssrc_, volume)
89 : media_channel_->SetDefaultOutputVolume(volume);
90}
91
92void AudioRtpReceiver::OnSetVolume(double volume) {
93 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
94 RTC_DCHECK_GE(volume, 0);
95 RTC_DCHECK_LE(volume, 10);
96 if (stopped_)
97 return;
98
99 cached_volume_ = volume;
100
101 // When the track is disabled, the volume of the source, which is the
102 // corresponding WebRtc Voice Engine channel will be 0. So we do not allow
103 // setting the volume to the source when the track is disabled.
104 if (track_->enabled()) {
105 worker_thread_->PostTask(
106 ToQueuedTask(worker_thread_safety_, [this, volume = cached_volume_]() {
107 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
108 SetOutputVolume_w(volume);
109 }));
110 }
111}

115 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);

119std::vector<std::string> AudioRtpReceiver::stream_ids() const {
120 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
121 std::vector<std::string> stream_ids(streams_.size());
122 for (size_t i = 0; i < streams_.size(); ++i)
123 stream_ids[i] = streams_[i]->id();
124 return stream_ids;
125}

127std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>
128AudioRtpReceiver::streams() const {
129 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
130 return streams_;
131}

133RtpParameters AudioRtpReceiver::GetParameters() const {
134 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
135 if (!media_channel_)
136 return RtpParameters();
137 return ssrc_ ? media_channel_->GetRtpReceiveParameters(*ssrc_)
138 : media_channel_->GetDefaultRtpReceiveParameters();

141void AudioRtpReceiver::SetFrameDecryptor(
142 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor) {
143 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
144 frame_decryptor_ = std::move(frame_decryptor);
145 // Special Case: Set the frame decryptor to any value on any existing channel.
146 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_) {
147 media_channel_->SetFrameDecryptor(*ssrc_, frame_decryptor_);
148 }
149}

151rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface>
152AudioRtpReceiver::GetFrameDecryptor() const {
153 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
154 return frame_decryptor_;
155}

157void AudioRtpReceiver::Stop() {
158 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
159 // TODO(deadbeef): Need to do more here to fully stop receiving packets.
160 if (!stopped_) {
161 source_->SetState(MediaSourceInterface::kEnded);
162 stopped_ = true;
163 }
164
165 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&]() {
166 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
167 if (media_channel_)
168 SetOutputVolume_w(0.0);
169 SetMediaChannel_w(nullptr);
170 });
171}
172
173void AudioRtpReceiver::StopAndEndTrack() {
174 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
175 Stop();
176 track_->internal()->set_ended();
177}
178
179void AudioRtpReceiver::RestartMediaChannel(absl::optional<uint32_t> ssrc) {
180 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
181 bool ok = worker_thread_->Invoke<bool>(
182 RTC_FROM_HERE, [&, enabled = cached_track_enabled_,
183 volume = cached_volume_, was_stopped = stopped_]() {
184 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
185 if (!media_channel_) {
186 RTC_DCHECK(was_stopped);
187 return false; // Can't restart.
188 }
189
190 if (!was_stopped && ssrc_ == ssrc) {
191 // Already running with that ssrc.
192 RTC_DCHECK(worker_thread_safety_->alive());
193 return true;
194 }
195
196 if (!was_stopped) {
197 source_->Stop(media_channel_, ssrc_);
198 }
199
200 ssrc_ = std::move(ssrc);
201 source_->Start(media_channel_, ssrc_);
202 if (ssrc_) {
203 media_channel_->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(*ssrc_, delay_.GetMs());
204 }
205
206 Reconfigure(enabled, volume);
207 return true;
208 });
209
210 if (!ok)
211 return;
212
213 stopped_ = false;
214}
215
216void AudioRtpReceiver::SetupMediaChannel(uint32_t ssrc) {
217 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
218 RestartMediaChannel(ssrc);
219}
220
221void AudioRtpReceiver::SetupUnsignaledMediaChannel() {
222 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
223 RestartMediaChannel(absl::nullopt);
224}

227 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
228 return ssrc_.value_or(0);

241
242void AudioRtpReceiver::SetStreams(
243 const std::vector<rtc::scoped_refptr<MediaStreamInterface>>& streams) {
244 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
245 // Remove remote track from any streams that are going away.
246 for (const auto& existing_stream : streams_) {
247 bool removed = true;
248 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
249 if (existing_stream->id() == stream->id()) {
250 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(existing_stream.get(), stream.get());
251 removed = false;
252 break;
253 }
254 }
255 if (removed) {
256 existing_stream->RemoveTrack(track_);
257 }
258 }
259 // Add remote track to any streams that are new.
260 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
261 bool added = true;
262 for (const auto& existing_stream : streams_) {
263 if (stream->id() == existing_stream->id()) {
264 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(stream.get(), existing_stream.get());
265 added = false;
266 break;
267 }
268 }
269 if (added) {
270 stream->AddTrack(track_);
271 }
272 }
273 streams_ = streams;
274}

276std::vector<RtpSource> AudioRtpReceiver::GetSources() const {
277 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
278 if (!media_channel_ || !ssrc_) {
279 return {};
280 }
281 return media_channel_->GetSources(*ssrc_);
282}

284void AudioRtpReceiver::SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
285 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer) {
286 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
287 if (media_channel_) {
288 media_channel_->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(ssrc_.value_or(0),
289 frame_transformer);
290 }
291 frame_transformer_ = std::move(frame_transformer);
292}
293
294// RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_)
295void AudioRtpReceiver::Reconfigure(bool track_enabled, double volume) {
296 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel_);
297
298 SetOutputVolume_w(track_enabled ? volume : 0);
299
300 if (ssrc_ && frame_decryptor_) {
301 // Reattach the frame decryptor if we were reconfigured.
302 media_channel_->SetFrameDecryptor(*ssrc_, frame_decryptor_);
303 }
304
305 if (frame_transformer_) {
306 media_channel_->SetDepacketizerToDecoderFrameTransformer(
307 ssrc_.value_or(0), frame_transformer_);
308 }
309}
310
311void AudioRtpReceiver::SetObserver(RtpReceiverObserverInterface* observer) {
312 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
313 observer_ = observer;
314 // Deliver any notifications the observer may have missed by being set late.
315 if (received_first_packet_ && observer_) {
316 observer_->OnFirstPacketReceived(media_type());
317 }
318}
319
320void AudioRtpReceiver::SetJitterBufferMinimumDelay(
321 absl::optional<double> delay_seconds) {
322 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
323 delay_.Set(delay_seconds);
324 if (media_channel_ && ssrc_)
325 media_channel_->SetBaseMinimumPlayoutDelayMs(*ssrc_, delay_.GetMs());
326}
327
328void AudioRtpReceiver::SetMediaChannel(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) {
329 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
330 RTC_DCHECK(media_channel == nullptr ||
331 media_channel->media_type() == media_type());
332
333 if (stopped_ && !media_channel)
334 return;
335
336 worker_thread_->Invoke<void>(RTC_FROM_HERE, [&] {
337 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
338 SetMediaChannel_w(media_channel);
339 });
340}
341
342// RTC_RUN_ON(worker_thread_)
343void AudioRtpReceiver::SetMediaChannel_w(cricket::MediaChannel* media_channel) {
344 media_channel ? worker_thread_safety_->SetAlive()
345 : worker_thread_safety_->SetNotAlive();
346 media_channel_ = static_cast<cricket::VoiceMediaChannel*>(media_channel);
347}
348
349void AudioRtpReceiver::NotifyFirstPacketReceived() {
350 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&signaling_thread_checker_);
351 if (observer_) {
352 observer_->OnFirstPacketReceived(media_type());
353 }
354 received_first_packet_ = true;
355}
